name: Room in Park Ave: Best location!
description: Superhost welcomes you to the "Pink Room": Peaceful, private room with comfortable, firm double bed in 1886 Victorian house in historic Park Ave area. Room faces east, tall windows, central AC. One block from cafes, restaurants; near highways, East Ave Historic District, Eastman Museum, RMSC, Zen Center, 1 mile from Memorial Art Gallery, 3 miles from U of Rochester. Driveway parking available depending on length of stay. Dogs by arrangement--$30 per stay.
neighborhood_overview: Beautiful historic neighborhood with lots of trees, old houses, interesting architecture, neighbors walking dogs, close to Park Ave with lots of cafes, restaurants, small stores, 7-Eleven, CVS. Great for walking around and looking at architecture.
host_about:
I'm a local professor,  living in Rochester since 2003 and loving it! I'm can recommend places to eat, drink and visit.  I work at home and during the pandemic I'm online a lot for work, yoga, church. I also do a lot of cooking and work around the house and garden. (Normally) I go out to the movies, music and restaurants a lot, or host my partner and friends. I'm a busy and active person.

I have a comfortable house and want guests to feel at home here, while respecting the fact that I work at home. I'm an early to bed (by 10:30) and early to rise (by 6:30) kind of person. Also an animal lover, especially dogs! I have a basset hound named Rowan who is very friendly. There are sometimes visiting dogs and the occasional other pet at my house and my partner comes over often. I have traveled to many parts of the world and lived in Costa Rica, Chile, Germany, France, and the UK. As a film and music buff,  for me living in Rochester is heaven--never a shortage of movies to see or concerts.

Guests share space in the fridge and kitchen to store food, if desired. If you want to cook, we can arrange a time. I have a well equipped and newly renovated kitchen to cook and eat in. The new back porch and garden is lovely to sit in as well.

name: Swiss Hospitality in the City
description: This is a guestroom with a queen size bed in a 3-bedroom house located on a quiet and tree lined neighborhood street. The bedroom is nicely furnished and is on the second floor. Two bicycles with helmets and lights are available for casual riding through town on a sunny day. Large discounts for weekly and monthly stays!
neighborhood_overview:
You will find stores and restaurants within 3 Minutes walking distance. For breakfast you have at least 3 choices for which you can get details on the web: James Brown's Place, Morningstar (Greek Restaurant), and Donuts Delite. For a local lunch or dinner you may enjoy Johnny's Irish Pub, the Merchant's Grill, the Merchant's Pasta House, or Paola's Mexican Restaurant. Within a couple of miles you can find great food at a decent price at Sinbad's (Mediterranean Food including Vegetarian) in the Park Ave area or Sticky Lips (BBQ) on the corner of Culver/Atlantic. If you like a fancier place there is Lento, Two Vine, and Pomodoro that I can recommend.
My location is very central as the Downtown is about 3 miles to the West, the University of Rochester is about 7 miles away, Xerox Webster is 10 miles to the East, and Rochester General is 2 miles to the N. The George Eastman House is about 2 miles to the S. The public library with a playground is less than half a mile away. Lake Ontar
host_about:
I am a Swiss engineer who came to this country in 1984 to continue my studies. In 1991 I joined Xerox and have been working in R&D ever since. My main hobbies are skiing and boarding in the winter time and hang gliding and biking in the summer. I also love hiking in the Finger Lakes area and visiting vineries for a little tasting. The week of the Rochester International Jazz Festival is a great time to take off work, enjoy the wonderful music, and try to see as many bands as possible.
My favorite engineer joke: how do you know you met an extravert engineer? He looks at YOUR shoes!
I speak English and German fluently, enjoy practicing my French and Spanish, and with hands and feet may be able to communicate in Italian. Needless to say I enjoy hosting people from all corners of the world.
I retired in March of 2016, so now I am traveling a bit more exploring other Airbnb homes. What fun!

name: Budget-friendly for Laid Back Travelers
description:
Come spend some time in our community-minded housing collective. We offer low-frills accommodations for the traveler on a budget.
We're close by to Eastman School of Music, George Eastman House, and the Rochester Public Market.
neighborhood_overview: Close by to nightlife, parks, good eats, and cafes, the Eastman School of Music and George Eastman House, the Rochester Public Market, the Riverside Convention Center and much, much more!
host_about: Coming from all ages and walks of life, RocHostel spans eight spacious houses (all clustered together) and consists of 20 full-time residents, two cats, and a bunny rabbit- all passionate about sustainability, social justice, community-building, and making the world a better place in general.  We have a large and continually expanding garden, are active in our community, organize various events throughout the month, and operate RocHostel where we provide guests like you with budget-friendly accommodations and help them to make the most out of their visits to Rochester.  If you're looking for a laidback, low-key, social place to stay, you've found it!

description: A lovely home right next to Park Avenue which holds great art and culture shops and adventures. This is also an ideal place if you are coming in for a conference, festival, or workshop at Eastman. Also great location for Jazz Fest or a graduation! You'll love this place because of it's location being walkable to so much and it is so close to Eastman, the UofR, RIT, downtown and so much more. Our place is great for couples, solo adventurers, and business travelers. We look forward to meeting you.
neighborhood_overview: The Park Ave area is incredibly walkable and gorgeous. The streets are lined with trees and Park Avenue has all sorts of shops, restaurants, and night life. However back in the neighborhoods where we live is quiet and an amazing neighborhood.
host_about:
We both grew up in Rochester, went away for college, and moved back to be near our families. We love to travel and have enjoyed getting to know people through Airbnb - both as hosts & guests. Greg works in healthcare consulting & Spencer leads the PT team at URMC.

We enjoy trying new things such as sports, scuba diving, and dancing. We are easy going and enjoy meeting people and exploring new areas.

name: Park Ave-Home Office Bedroom
description: Brand new double/full size bed with new mattress in sunny bedroom office in historic 1886 Victorian house with lovely art/antiques. One of 2 guest rooms, shared bathroom upstairs, 2nd bathroom downstairs. Friendly basset hound in residence. I often use this space daytimes depending on my schedule--but I work downstairs when guests are in. LGBTQI friendly. Near Park Ave cafes/restaurants, East Ave Historic District,   UR (3 mi.), RIT (5 mi.). One shared driveway parking space available.
neighborhood_overview:
LOCAL AMENITIES/DIRECTIONS
If you walk to the end of Donlon St, left out of the house, (it’s a dead end for cars) you can zigzag through the alley to Park Ave. To your right are: Baker St Bakery, Wine Sense wine store, Boulder Café, hair salons, dry cleaners, restaurants (Sinbad’s is excellent and cheap; Esan Thai across the street is also good as is the Mexican restaurants). To your left on Park Ave are CVS drugstore, a bank/ATM, and further down is a nice café, Jembetat, across the street from 7-11, a larger convenience store.

Heading north on Culver at University there is a no-frills grocery store Price Rite; heading east on Park Ave, if you follow it all the way to its end it curves around and dead ends onto East Ave. A couple blocks further east (to the right) you will find Wegman’s grocery store, a liquor store, Dunkin’ Donuts, a gym, etc.

Heading west on East Ave towards downtown, from Berkeley St you will come to Breathe Yoga next to the Eastman House

name: Luxuriously Remodeled 1BD Apt#2 in 1906 Mansion
description: Our most luxuriously remodeled & fully furnished 1 bedroom apartment on the 1st floor. Large, bright living room with 9′ ceilings, hardwoods, original moldings, & a fireplace, opens to a brand new kitchen, island with seating. Redesigned en suite marble bathroom & glass shower with entrance close to living room. Recently installed split/wall AC/Heat units in the living room and bedroom provide year-round comfort. Reserved off-street parking included. Walk to Park Ave stores/shops/restaurants.
neighborhood_overview:
This luxurious apartment is in a beautiful mansion on the corner of Argyle St & East Ave in the East Avenue Historic District. Within one block is Park Ave with numerous shops, cafes, restaurants, sights (George Eastman House, Memorial Art Gallery, Rochester Museum & Science Center) all within walking distance. Wonderful walking/biking neighborhood surrounded by mansions, an historic Frank Lloyd Wright restored home, Wegmans (Rochester's "Taj Mahal of grocery stores" according to Consumer Reports!), sightseeing, and many natural parks.

Located in one of Rochester's most scenic and vibrant neighborhoods, the East Avenue Historic District is near The George Eastman Museum (Kodak founder) surrounded by other mansions & historic homes with convenience shops, grocery stores, landmarks, cafes, restaurants, churches, parks within walking distance. If you like going out, you are directly near the heart of Rochester's nightlife with wonderful dining.
host_about: We're both professionals, Ed's a recently retired teacher and Tom's a Realtor. As owners of a furnished 8-apartment historic property here in Rochester, we truly enjoy getting away to travel a few times/year and appreciate quality, clean accommodations in safe, easy to walk/ride locations where we can explore parks, good restaurants, and local culture.

name: 2 story, 2 bedroom house near UR
description: This furnished whole house consists of a fully-equipped first floor kitchen, dining room & living room, and 2 bedrooms and a bath upstairs.  Each bedroom has a 2 person bed-  a king in one and a queen in the other.  It's at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac. There's a small yard, and space for 1 or 2 cars to park directly in front of the house, end-to-end. A washer and dryer are provided in the basement.
neighborhood_overview: I love the neighborhood's proximity to the Genesee River Trail System, the University of Rochester, downtown Rochester, expressways, and the airport. There are few shops and services nearby, but by car we are 5-15 minutes from everything Rochester has to offer.  The neighborhood is by  no means "upscale" or a "destination"- it's mixed socioeconomically, with some well-kept homes and other houses and businesses that could use some loving care. Guests have *not* had safety or security issues; we just recommend common-sense precautions like not leaving valuables in cars, locking exterior doors and latching ground floor windows (and using the optional alarm system, if you wish), and not walking alone at night.
host_about: I work in community development both as an employee of a community development credit union and as a property owner-manager committed to neighborhood revitalization that benefits everyone- especially long-term, lower-income residents.

name: Eclectic Private Home in Swillburg/SouthWedge
description: Relax and explore the Rochester area from my 1920's home. Everything you need for long-term stays. It is walking distance to many great restaurants, parks, shops and bars. Private access to the house with a queen size bed in the upstairs bedroom and a full size bed in the downstairs bedroom. Free street parking. High speed internet and workspace. Easy check in with key pad lock! Please read the full description below before booking.
neighborhood_overview: The house is set in Rochester’s Swillburg neighborhood, across the street from a leafy park. The neighborhood has a family-friendly feel and is ethnically and economically diverse. A variety of restaurants, shops, cafes, and bars are a short walk away. Located a short 5-min drive to the University of Rochester and a 14-min drive to RIT.
host_about: I love traveling and opening my home to others on their travels. I'm happy to share any recommendations on fun things to do in Rochester! My partner and I have one son who is now a toddler. We haven't been able to travel much during the pandemic but we are eager to start taking tips again. Some of my favorite places I've visited are Ireland, Newfoundland, New Orleans and Amsterdam.

name: Historic Home by UofR,Apt 1 is Charming & Private
description: Our Riverside Apt.  Sunny, 2 level apt, in rear of house,  a short walk to the U of R with plenty of space/parking.  One bedroom with lots of character as well as a futon in the living room in restored mansion on Mt. Hope.  There is a fully equipped kitchen, spiral staircase, and 1 and 1/2 baths. It has a separate entrance, and is approximately 1,000 square feet.  Set on a peaceful acre of land along the Genesee River. Enjoy Rochester from this historic mansion with tons of character and charm.
neighborhood_overview: We  moved to this amazing house in September 2014 and have been working non-stop to restore some of it's original beauty.  We are bordered by the U of R property and the U of R provost lives across the street!   We are close to downtown and the South Wedge has lots of great eateries and pubs as well as a new microbrewery steps down the hill.  Our house is on an acre of land overlooking the river and the U of R.  We are 4 houses away from beautiful Mount Hope Cemetary.
host_about:
Fun loving teachers who have traveled a bit and spent plenty of time on someone else's sofa.  Mike used to be a chef but is now a culinary professor at the local community college.  Laura is a Middle School Math teacher in the city.  

We have  decided to share our home with other travelers after we stayed in some friendly homes in Ireland. We have been having guests for over a year now and it has been a 100% positive experience.

name: Updated 1Bedroom Apt#6 in 1906 Mansion
description: Recently updated & completely furnished apartment on the third floor of a Claude Bragdon-designed 1906 mansion. Spacious living room, fireplace and hardwood floors. neighborhood_overview: Within a few blocks of numerous shops, cafes, sights (George Eastman House, Memorial Art Gallery, Rochester Museum & Science Center) all within walking distance. name: 1 Bedroom in a great neighborhood near everything!
description: This is a shared, owner & dog occupied, east side city colonial home minutes from Museums, Art Galleries, Shops, Entertainment Venues, Breweries, etc.  Walk to Casual & Fine Dining Restaurants, Sports Bars, Convenient Stores, Golf, Buf Bills Camp, Parks & Nature Trails. Lake Ontario/Beach/Bay & Finger Lakes region are a short drive.  Off Street Parking,  fenced yard, large deck/gazebo, fire pit.  Multi-room space has kitchen amenities. Eco-friendly.  Come & enjoy all that Rochester has to offer!
neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is called the North Winton Village and was a runner up in our City Newspaper's 2015 BEST OF ROCHESTER neighborhoods category.   Residents are friendly and watch out for one another.   It is a mixed age neighborhood and includes many single people and also  families with children.  You'll notice a lot of people out walking their dogs, walking with friends, jogging and riding bikes as our streets have shared bike lanes.  There are several casual, sports, and fine dining restaurants, a wine bar, convenient store, liquor store, hiking trails, parks and more all within walking distance.  Nearby and just a few minutes down the road is Wegmans, Aldis, Price Rite and other grocery and specialty stores, gas stations, pizza shops, bagels and donuts shops, diners, and the wonderful Mayer's hardware store.  Major attractions, museums, art galleries, a planetarium, a comedy club, bowling/entertainment center, micro breweries, antique shops and more are in very close proximity.
host_about: Fun and knowledgeable. Some personal interests include the arts, performing arts, music, classic cars, fine wine and food, conservation and preservation, animal welfare and go green initiatives.  I have degrees in Liberal Arts, Business Administration, Marketing and an MBA from St. John Fisher University.  I left the corporate world a few years ago and am now managing the business that I started in 2007.

The centrally located Historic Cornhill district provides convenient access to best that Rochester has to offer -- from downtown businesses to boutique shops, theater to sporting events, and world-class concerts to innovative craft breweries. Amid stunning 19th Century architecture, the location affords nearby trails for running or strolling along the Genesee River. You can leave the car behind and find amazing cultural, dining, and networking opportunities just around the corner.

For those craving a little nightlife, local destinations cater to every preference. Visit Rochester’s Calendar for seasonal events that attract thousands. Please reference my guidebook for a list of local restaurants, bars, entertainment, parks, museums, sightseeing attractions, and other unique activities.

name: Stylish Studio w/Balcony in Historic Corn Hill
description: Stay in Rochester's oldest residential neighborhood among many beautiful Victorian homes. Walk to grab a glass of wine at Flight Wine bar or take a scenic stroll along the Genesee River. Right off 490, this apartment is close to airport, city center, University of Rochester, Strong Memorial Hospital, Highland Hospital, College Town, & South Wedge. Walk to downtown attractions such as Blue Cross Arena (0.5miles-10min walk), Dinosaur BBQ (0.5miles-10min walk) & Frontier Field (0.7miles-15min walk)
neighborhood_overview: Welcome to the oldest residential neighborhood in Rochester, NY. This historic neighborhood sits on the banks of Genesee River and is full of tree lined streets and beautiful Victorian homes. It is home to the biggest summer festival in Rochester, Corn Hill Arts Festival, which takes place July 13th and 14th in 2019. Corn Hill landing is about a 7 minute walk from the apartment and has 5 restaurants, coffee shop, a wine bar, sports bar, and a small convenience store.
host_about: My husband and I Iove meeting people from different parts of the world and look forward to connecting with you as hosts or travelers.  We will do our best to make your stay as comfortable as possible or be good guests, depending on our role.

host_about:
Hello and welcome to our Airbnb loft page!

My fiancé Heather and I have traveled to many parts of the country for work and pleasure. While doing so, we have enjoyed a wide variety of places offered on Airbnb. Having experienced staying in other hosts' spaces, all the while traveling and meeting new people, we decided we would like hosting as well. Our loft/studio and gallery space is now available for anyone looking for that unique experience while traveling to Rochester. 
We look forward to hosting you!

Tim

name: Fresh Retreat Off Of Park Avenue
description: We have the best of both worlds. We are on a quiet street right between the action of both Park and Monroe Avenue, only a short stroll to cafes, restaurants, and bars. Our spot in the Park Ave Neighborhood is a convenient 5 minutes into downtown Rochester and 10-20 minutes from the universities: St. John Fisher, Nazareth, U of R, and RIT.
neighborhood_overview: We are situated in the Park Ave Neighborhood within short walking distance to the Monroe Village Neighborhood. Park Ave is Rochester's best-known neighborhood for strolling and shopping in an urban environment. You’ll find an eclectic mix of residential and commercial properties, including restaurants, bars, retail, and salons.  Monroe Village is probably Rochester's funkiest neighborhood. Monroe Village after dark is a nightlife district with a casual, laid-back atmosphere. Lined with bars and independent restaurants, it is very much the place to go if you prefer jeans and t-shirt. By day, Monroe Village is a true indie shopping destination, with unique stores selling everything from antiques to trendy clothing to fair trade goods.
host_about:
Hi! My name is Katie and my husband Garrett and I host our home in the Historic Park Ave Neighborhood of the fantastic Western NY city of Rochester. I am originally from Miami FL and Garrett is from the small town of Mt. Morris in the greater Rochester region.

 Garrett and I met while attending Rochester Institute of Technology. Garrett went for mechanical engineering and I went for medical illustration. It's your typical nerd meets artist love story.

We frequently enjoy traveling to visit my family in South Florida. We are active with community service projects in our city. We also love movies, boardgames, biking, rock climbing, and snowboarding when the weather is right. Garrett attends rock climbing competitions in our area. You will find a few of my paintings on the walls of our home and maybe you'll also find a few on the walls of our city.

You can find fun things to see in Rochester on (Hidden by Airbnb) @explorerochester 

We are passionate about our neighborhood. We love our City of Rochester. We hope you get to enjoy everything this area has to offer.

name: Swiss Hospitality Guest Room
description: This is a guestroom with a queen size bed in a 3-bedroom house located on a quiet and tree lined neighborhood street. The bedroom is nicely furnished and is on the second floor. Two bicycles with helmets and lights are available for casual riding through town on a sunny day. Large discounts for weekly and monthly stays!
neighborhood_overview:
You will find stores and restaurants within 3 Minutes walking distance. For breakfast you have at least 3 choices for which you can get details on the web: James Brown's Place, Morningstar (Greek Restaurant), and Donuts Delite. For a local lunch or dinner you may enjoy Johnny's Irish Pub, the Merchant's Grill, the Merchant's Wood Fired Pizza . Within a couple of miles you can find great food at a decent price at Sinbad's (Mediterranean Food including Vegetarian) in the Park Ave area or Sticky Lips (BBQ) on the corner of Culver/Atlantic. If you like a fancier place there is Lento, Two Vine, and Pomodoro that I can recommend.
My location is very central as the Downtown is about 3 miles to the West, the University of Rochester is about 7 miles away, Xerox Webster is 10 miles to the East, and Rochester General is 2 miles to the N. The George Eastman House is about 2 miles to the S. The public library with a playground is less than half a mile away. Lake Ontario with the Sea Breeze Am
host_about:
I am a Swiss engineer who came to this country in 1984 to continue my studies. In 1991 I joined Xerox and have been working in R&D ever since. My main hobbies are skiing and boarding in the winter time and hang gliding and biking in the summer. I also love hiking in the Finger Lakes area and visiting vineries for a little tasting. The week of the Rochester International Jazz Festival is a great time to take off work, enjoy the wonderful music, and try to see as many bands as possible.
My favorite engineer joke: how do you know you met an extravert engineer? He looks at YOUR shoes!
I speak English and German fluently, enjoy practicing my French and Spanish, and with hands and feet may be able to communicate in Italian. Needless to say I enjoy hosting people from all corners of the world.
I retired in March of 2016, so now I am traveling a bit more exploring other Airbnb homes. What fun!

name: Spacious Renovated City Home - Averill House
description: Averill House was built in 1840 and completely renovated. This spacious, airy house features a large updated kitchen, two full baths, off street parking, a huge yard, and 3 bedrooms. A large front sun porch offers additional room for hanging out. The house offers vintage charm plus all the conveniences of today in a beautiful setting, convenient to many local amenities. Directly across the street from one of our other airbnbs, perfect for large families looking to stay close to each other.
neighborhood_overview: The South Wedge Neighborhood is conveniently located close to downtown Rochester and is minutes from Strong Memorial Hospital, Highland Hospital, and Golisano Children’s Hospital. The neighborhood includes a natural foods grocery store across the street from the house, many restaurants and shops, a craft brewery, and many nightlife options. Highland Park and Mt. Hope Cemetery are within walking distance and offer beautiful scenic views.
host_about: I’m a small business owner who lives in the South Wedge neighborhood near our two Airbnb properties. My interests are history and art, I love to do historical research and also enjoy anything creative. My partner, Jim, and I have enjoyed restoring our home and the Airbnb’s and have tried to maintain some of their original features and respect the era in which they were built. Our business, Historic Houseparts, is a retail business that specializes in architectural salvage, restoration supplies and vintage decorative accessories. We’ve used lots of our products in our houses. We also love to travel! So we’ve tried to make our houses feel like places we’d love to stay if we were traveling.

neighborhood_overview:
A favourite with visitors, Neighbourhood of the Arts (NOTA) has it all…art, history, culture, surprises on every corner; no wonder that it draws so many visitors!

• Full calendar of festivals and events year round; perfect destination for the solo adventure seeker, business traveller, couples, or family and friends. We are located right in the heart of it all!

• A short distance from the other great local neighbourhoods (Park Avenue, Downtown, Corn Hill, South Wedge, Highland Park)

• Only a few minutes walk to the city’s top museums, galleries, eateries and shops.

SOME IDEAS:

• Check out Art Walk, Memorial Art Gallery (3 min walk) or Rochester Museum & Science Centre (5 min walk)

• Got kids? Head over the the Strong National Museum of Play (3 min drive or 15 min walk)

• Take a stroll over to Village Gate Square (8 min walk) and check out some local art and grab a bite at Good Luck.

• For a quick p
host_about:
A proud Torontonian, a lucky mother of three, a lover of travel, an avid reader, an adorer of beautiful things, a spiritual seeker, a creator of guilt-free, but still ridiculously delicious meals.
Always on the hunt for the best coffee, almond croissants, fish tacos and pizza.  Love to explore, love to adventure.  Love to connect with others.

As my husband Sam started spending more time south of the border for work, we quickly discovered that we really really loved the feel of this part of Rochester.  Every time I venture out on foot, I find something new, something beautiful, something unexpected.  There’s a little something here for everyone, and we are really excited for you to experience the same.

We’ve travelled to many places over the years (though it never seems quite enough!).  We’ve used Airbnb as our preferred choice for almost a decade.  Both in our own city, as well as clear across the globe, we’ve discovered that it’s such great way to travel.  We get to meet interesting and amazing people, live like locals, discover hidden gems in any given place, enjoy the comfort and flexibility of extra space and the comforts of home (like separate sleeping quarters for us and the kids, or a kitchen to prep quick meals and stash local treats we find along our way).  

So our goal is to host you the way we love to be hosted, bringing together the best experiences we’ve had and share them here with you in our very own way!

description: Cozy, well stocked studio apartment in a 4-story brick building. Guests of varying backgrounds are welcome! Feel like a local in our apartment in the heart of our city.
neighborhood_overview:
The building is located in a bustling and vibrant neighborhood within walking distance to the southwedge neighborhood.

From the studio, driving estimates and distances:
Rochester Airport: 10 minutes, 7.3 miles
Eastman School of Music: 4 minutes, 0.9 miles
George Eastman House: 6 minutes, 1.7 miles
Geva Theater: 3 minutes, 0.6 miles
UofR campus: 9 minutes, 2.3 miles
RIT campus: 17 minutes, 5.8 miles
Blue Cross Arena: 5 minutes, 1.0 mile
Public Library: 4 minutes, 0.9 miles
Auditorium Theater: 6 minutes, 1.2 miles

Nearby fast food restaurants include Burger King, McDonalds, Dunkin Donuts, Bruegger's, as well as, a variety of well established sit down restaurants including some of my personal favorites, The Owl House, Cedar Lebanese restaurant and Aladdin's Natural Eatery (Mediterranean, good for vegetarians) and La Casa (Mexican).

Nick's Super Store is a small grocery store, just a few blocks away.
host_about:
I love to read, exercise and spend time with my family.  I also enjoy cooking and baking.   My favorite season is the summer. We have 2 beautiful daughters and 2 adorable Lhasapoos named Angel and Flash.

Travel is my passion! I've had the pleasure to study abroad in Mexico, live in Italy, backpack and travel through various countries and states. 

I'm always looking for a new adventure! 

My favorite book is "The Red Tent". My family loves it when I make my "famous" carrot cake.

description: Come and Enjoy The Best of Rochester City Living.  Have a Nice, Comfy Private Room to yourself.  Rochester General Hospital, East Ridge Road Restaurants, Wegmans, Walmart, Target and only from The University of Rochester (UofR). Downtown, Strong Memorial Hospital and only Minutes to RIT. neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a city neighborhood on the border of beautiful Irondequoit township.  There is mostly professional homeowners on this block and surrounding blocks. host_about:
Rosa is a Writer & a retired LMSW & Behavioral Therapist. James the founder of JimGCoachingClub-com 
is an international Real estate Coach, Mentor & Investor. 

They've been in a loving marriage of over 30  yrs and are the parents of 5 beautiful children.

Their focus is always on serving their  clients with honesty, integrity and discretion as a dependable and knowledgeable experts in their respective fields and are committed to exceptional results.

They enjoy working with people and giving back to the community. They both also donate many hours and personal resources coaching, mentoring & advising young adults from all walks of life in Rochester and its surrounding areas.

James devotes much of his time & resources helping the homeless men, women and children in WNY.

Rosa & James are believers and faithful followers of Jesus Christ. They have a heart to bring a knowledge of the love, grace and mercy of Jesus Christ to everyone they meet &/or work with, either by their walk &/or their words.

name: Stylish Studio w/porch in the Heart of Park Ave
description: Stay in the heart of Park Ave, one of Rochester's best-known neighborhoods for strolling & shopping in an urban environment. This freshly renovated studio apartment offers all the modern comforts & conveniences. Enjoy a cup of coffee on the porch or browse the web using our fast wifi. Once you’ve worked up an appetite, check out one of many cafes, coffee shops (including Starbucks), bars, & restaurants that are literally steps away. Close to 490/590, airport, downtown, many colleges/universities
neighborhood_overview:
Park Avenue is lined with specialty shops, small businesses of every description, and local restaurants and cafes that extend onto the sidewalks during the summer months. Neighborhood residents enjoy convenient access to daily necessities. Right on the Avenue are banks, salons, a pharmacy, bakeries, florist, bars, coffee shops, a veterinarian, a mailing/copy. Each August the Park Avenue Merchants Association hosts one of the oldest neighborhood festivals in the city, the Park Avenue Summer Art Festival, and each December rings in the holidays with the Park Avenue Holiday Open House.

All along Park Avenue and down its side streets are handsome homes of all shapes and sizes— single-family houses, beautiful brick apartment buildings, and converted multi-unit dwellings. From sprawling Tudor mansions to modest Princess Anne cottages, from the stately apartments to elaborate Queen Anne homesteads, nearly every block of the neighborhood holds historic treasures.

name: Quiet, Modernized Apt in Historic Arts District
description: Beautifully remodeled quiet apartment in the heart of Rochester's arts and cultural district.  Minutes walk from museums, performing arts theatres, restaurants, cafés, art galleries and micro-breweries.  Split bath allows for use of the vanity while toilet/shower is occupied.  All windows replaced in 2023.  Owners live on property.  Full kitchen with utensils, stacked laundry, lightning fast wifi, giant 55" UHD Smart TV, and everything you will need for your home away from home.
neighborhood_overview: Located in the Neighborhood of the Arts (NOTA), sites like the George Eastman Museum, the Rochester Museum and Science Center, the Strong (National Museum of Play), the Memorial Art Gallery, the Kodak Theatre, Rochester Auditorium Theatre, and many quaint music venues are a 2 to 20 minute walk away.  The Park Ave district is just up the street featuring unique restaurants, cafés, and shops.  Village Gate is a couple of blocks away and is a truly unique Rochester experience for food, drinks, and shopping.  There are seven local micro-breweries: Three-Heads, Rohrbach, Roc Brewing, Lost Borough, Sager Beer Works, Nine Maidens, and Fairport Brewery.  It's around one mile to the Rochester International Jazz Festival (June).  The entertainment district (East and Alexander), with many bars and clubs, is less than a mile away.
host_about:
We love to travel!  Many of the amenities we offer were inspired by some of the things we appreciated (or didn't) at the places we've stayed.  Our travels include driving the East and West coasts of the USA, Alaska, Hawaii, Disney and Universal theme parks, Europe, and several Caribbean islands.  We look forward to many more years of exploring!

We love our city and we're happy to give recommendations for food, drink, and fun things to do.

Cozy three bedroom home on a quiet street near Kodak Theatre. University of Rochester / Strong Memorial Hospital, Rochester Institute of Technology within easy driving range. Close to Seneca Park Zoo and many other attractions. Off street parking.

As a former college football player, my passions are pretty predictable: working out, college football & the NFL, and local cuisine.

I can't say enough good things about Rochester. I think the city gets a bad rep because of the cold winters, but the food scene, beautiful seasons, access to finger lakes, and sense of community is second to none. 

Ask me about my favorite brewery or favorite place to get a garbage plate :)

host_about:
I am a hatmaker (milliner), textile artist and grant writer, and I live in Rochester, NY.  My son Eli is a musician/videographer, and he sometimes lives here as well.  We like to go great places...we both have a lot of energy.  We both value creativity and respect that people have all kinds of various approaches to life. I believe that with consideration and communication we can figure it out so that everyone is happy.

I also teach felting classes, and indigo dyeing (shibori) classes - and hat making in my studio.  I like to have a bicycle to get around town for errands close by, and love walking my dog and getting to know neighbors and the neighborhood. 

I think it's important to get out and live life!  I also like to create safe and welcoming spaces to return to with textiles and art from around the world that are relaxing and beautiful.

host_about:
I am a long time Rochester Resident. My love of travelling has taken me all over the world, but I always love coming back home to Rochester and its beautiful 4 seasons weather.

I am a professional photographer and you would enjoy some of my photographs in my properties.

My college town properties are located at a walking distance to the U of R and Strong memorial hospital, highland hospital and highland park. neighborhood_overview:
Historic Corn Hill, or as it was dubbed, "the ruffled shirt district" when established in the mid 1800's, is located on the west bank of the Genesee River and adjacent to downtown Rochester. It is a residential neighborhood with restaurants and shops along the river, a 5 minute walk. Corn Hill is unique because of a strong neighborhood association and the famed Corn Hill Festival, occurring in mid July and the Holiday Historic House Tour, held in early December.
In general, Rochester has non stop festivals from mid May (Lilac Festival), the 10 day International Jazz Festival in June, on through September, (Fringe Festival), and right up to the holidays.
host_about:
As a native Rochestarian, and 25 years in this home, I know of many of the local gems and can help you get around Rochester.  Whether you're in the pursuit of food, culture or nature walks, I welcome the opportunity to help make your stay satisfying.  I can be as visible or invisible as you'd like. I enjoy meeting people of different backgrounds, exchanging stories and ideas.  I've traveled to several locations in Europe, New Zealand, Tasmania and Central America, along with fairly extensive travel throught the U.S.  
My education and training from Syracuse University was in Clinical Social Work. My career was at the University of Rochester Medical Center. Now I'm retired and spending time volunteering and exploring. 
My life motto is "We all do better, when we all do better."

One of the bedroom suites is located on the first level. There is also a large wraparound balcony accessible from the first level. The second floor has a bedroom suite with a bath, office area, family room, and a wonderful cozy patio. Two stories of windows provide a delightfully bright interior with views of nearby parks.
neighborhood_overview: Many types of shops, ethnic restaurants and local taverns within walking distance to the complex. It is one of the more eclectic neighborhoods in the city. The complex is also within walking distance to Highland Park a large well designed park for walkers and hikers. Easy on/off access to Highway 490 and only a mile from downtown Rochester.

name: Ellwanger Guest House,  by U of R
description: Looking for peace & quiet? Elbow room? Relocating professor? Ellwanger Estate Guest House is a stately updated Victorian home with 4,200 square feet, and 3BD/2.5BA. Located in the historic Mt Hope/Highland Preservation District, with its well manicured historic gardens, it is in one of the most beautiful areas of the city. Our place is great for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, and families.
neighborhood_overview:
Rochester, New York, United States
The University of Rochester neighborhood is one of the most prestigious areas of the city. Many of the homes date back to the Victorian era and were owned by some of Rochester's most famous residents. The neighborhood is known as the Mt. Hope/Highland Historic District. You are (a hardy) walking distance from the U of R, and main center of the South Wedge. Both are beautiful, safe communities within the City of Rochester.
host_about:
I love hospitality! I attend to every detail in making the Ellwanger Guest House a premier hosting destination. 

In 2019, I purchased the horribly dilapidated Ellwanger Guest House, adjacent to the “Ellwanger Gardens”, both with great historical significance. I stumbled upon this diamond in the rough and found that I needed it as much as it needed me, it was love at first sight.

 I have spent the last year lovingly restoring the Ellwanger Guest House to bring it back to its original glory. Today the Ellwanger Guest House is once again a jewel of Rochester, and hosting guests from around the world.

name: Modernized 1920 Home: Walk to URMC, Highland Park
description:
Great location, located in Rochester and borders Brighton. Conveniently located to highways and approximately 4 miles to the airport. Walking distance to college town with plenty of restaurants. About 2-3 miles to Park Ave area, downtown area, art gallery, museums and more.

Restored and refinished hardwoods floors, gum wood and fully renovated inside.

Great front porch, nice backyard to enjoy & relax or having dinner outside.

Roughly 10-15 minutes to RIT, Nazareth and St. John Fischer.
neighborhood_overview:
Quite and peaceful neighborhood. Great location, walking distance to URMC, Highland Park, College Town (Restaurants, shops, Starbucks, Chipotle etc.). It’s located in City of Rochester and borders Brighton.

Convenient to the highways and about 4 miles to the airport. Centrally located, less than 3 miles to Park Ave area, downtown, art gallery, and Science museums (2.5 mi), Strong Museum of Play (2.3 mi) and more.... Short drive, about10-15 minutes to RIT, St. John Fisher, Nazareth, Eastman School of Music, Convention Centre. 45 min from Bristol Mtn for skiing and a day trip to the Finger Lake wine trails and Niagara Falls.

Distillery is a restaurant/bar started in Rochester, and is one block from the house. It has multiple locations throughout Rochester, this location is the first one in Rochester. Local bakery right around the corner.
host_about: I am passionate about sports, travelling new places. I majored in Journalism and Sport Management and love my time with friends and my mother!

name: ❤️CollegTown/UR Medprofessionals office cozyapt❤️
description: Imagine yourself in this cozy open floor studio ideal for work from home office space and Business trips that is within a short walking distance to UofR, URMC and Highland Hospital.Ideally located within 10 minute walk to Fine dinning, Starbucks, fast food and 20 minutes walk to Highland hospital and Highland park- venue of the Lilac festival. Well equipped kitchenette, queen bed in the screened off area and a full sized sofa bed.  Nice desk for your computer/business needs.
neighborhood_overview: The apartment is at a walking distance to Starbucks, Burger king, McDonald, and Fine dinning in the college town. 15 minutes walk to Highland park- the site for world famous lilac festival of Rochester that takes place around Mothers day. host_about:
I am a long time Rochester Resident. My love of travelling has taken me all over the world, but I always love coming back home to Rochester and its beautiful 4 seasons weather.

I am a professional photographer and you would enjoy some of my photographs in my properties.
I have seen my fair share of hotels and Airbnb houses on my travels around the world and understand the needs of fellow travellers. As a host, I can’t wait to show fellow travellers the same great hospitality that I have had across the globe.

My college town properties are located at a walking distance to the U of R and Strong memorial hospital, highland hospital and highland park. These are specifically organized to cater to professionals like physicians, nurses, medical students and other U of R visitors so they can live in a convenient place to work and can walk to their work or interviews etc. these are also well suited for guests visiting family locally or at these hospitals or coming to town for one of many festivals including world famous Lilacs festival. In all of our properties you will have the entire place to yourself. I am always available to answer any questions..

name: 2 bedroom house w/ 2 double & 2 twin beds, near UR
description: This furnished whole house consists of a fully-equipped first floor kitchen, dining room & living room, and 2 bedrooms and a bath upstairs.  Each bedroom has a 2 person (full/double) bed and a twin bed. (The twin beds are not shown in the photos, but are present.)  There's a small front porch, and an adjacent shaded green space for relaxing outdoors. 2 cars can park end-to-end in the driveway to the left of the house, steps from the front door. A washer and dryer are provided in the basement.
neighborhood_overview: I love my neighborhood's proximity to the Genesee River Trail System, the University of Rochester, downtown Rochester, expressways, and the airport. There are few shops and services nearby, but by car we are 5-15 minutes from everything Rochester has to offer.  The neighborhood is by  no means "upscale" or a "destination"- it's mixed socioeconomically, with some well-kept homes and other houses and businesses that could use some loving care. Guests have *not* had safety or security issues; we just recommend common-sense precautions like not leaving valuables in cars, locking exterior doors and latching ground floor windows (and using the optional alarm system, if you wish), and not walking alone at night.
host_about: I work in community development both as an employee of a community development credit union and as a property owner-manager committed to neighborhood revitalization that benefits everyone- especially long-term, lower-income residents.

name: Beautiful Rochester Home in Quaint Neighborhood
description: This comfortable and cozy home has beautiful original gum wood trim, hardwood floors, an updated kitchen, large screen tv, washer/dryer, sunroom, formal dining room. A backyard with a brick patio for your enjoyment. During the summer, there is a grill and patio furniture available. It is close to everything!  Trendy eateries, RIT, MCC, U of R, Strong Hospital (w/i walking distance) and Highland Hospital. Genesee Valley Park, Rochester Airport, expressways, Downtown Rochester and so much more!
neighborhood_overview: Our home is centrally located and wonderfully convenient to downtown Rochester, just minutes away from the Rochester International airport, the University of Rochester, RIT, MCC, shopping, fine culinary restaurants to varied mix of cultural foods, and grocery stores like Trader Joes, Aldi's and Wegmans, (a Rochester must shop).  Within walking distance are restaurants, coffee shops, shopping, Strong Memorial Hospital,  Highland Hospital, Ronald McDonald House, beauty/salon services, a bike shop, auto repair.  Also walking distance there are plenty of  recreational areas such as Genesee Valley Park with golf course, and  the Erie Canal bike trail where you'll see walkers, runners and bikers enjoying all the beauty that the trail has to offer. There's even an outside teal colored gym just west of the house off the trail. It's a wonderful neighborhood with a mix of professionals and students.

description:

Great for a long term stay

Welcome to your private, beautiful beach stay where antique design is enhanced with a modern touch. It spreads over 2 spacious stories and is in one of the most amazing locations in Rochester. People come from all areas to enjoy our famous, Ontario beach.The area is packed with restaurants, bars and ice cream parlors!

P.S. Camera is placed in the front of house
neighborhood_overview:
10 minute drive to downtown and it’s conveniently placed where you’re away from busy city life but still close to downtown for your business needs or exploring desires

The beach is a literal 5 minute walk from the property. If the beach isn’t on your list that day, you are a 4 minute walk from amazing, popular dining. Taste of Bahamas, Windjammers bar and grill, Lakesiders bar, Char pit, Abbotts Ice cream. Etc. those are just a few places that are in 5 minutes walking distance. In the mornings, you can also walk 5 minutes to Pats coffee shop which is right on the beach!

The neighborhood and safe and quiet. Loud gathering and guests would not permitted on this property. You can walk to the beach/ marina for all gatherings and get togethers!

Rosa is a Writer & a retired LMSW & Behavioral Therapist. James the founder of JimGCoachingClub-com

They've been in a loving marriage of over 30  yrs and are the parents of 5 beautiful children.

Their focus is always on serving their  clients with honesty, integrity and discretion as a dependable and knowledgeable experts in their respective fields and are committed to exceptional results.

name: Apartment in Corn Hill Preservation District
description: The apartment in a 4-unit apartment building, located in the Corn Hill Preservation District. Corning Hill Landing, with bars, restaurants, and a convenience store, is just four blocks away on the banks of the Genesee River. name: The Royal Cottage
description: Admittedly, the Queen Charlotte Royal Cottage is not for everyone. This Airbnb location is intended to have guests experience the royal charm and vivacity of a Queen Anne--style mansion built 114 years ago. It is situated at the highest point of Rochester, the hot spot for Kodak’s innovations, cultural diversity, and park landscape architect designed by the famous Frederick Law Olmsted. Enjoy some of Rochester’s most prized local attractions just minutes from your stay.
neighborhood_overview:
Enjoy the royal charm and vivacity of this Queen Anne--style mansion built in 1907---over 113 years ago. When George Eastman founded Eastman Kodak on September 4, 1888, he later had many homes built near Kodak Park to attract executives during the early growth period. The Royal Escape is one of those homes. Whether you plan to work or escape during your stay, take the time to experience the same historic neighborhood that inspired such international leaders as Susan B. Anthony and Fredrick Douglas. This home is for those who appreciate the historic luxury of centuries past.
Inside you will find a Mansion and Tour Guide for historical insights and places to visit to enhance your enjoyment during your stay. In addition, the Guest Rules are included to help you locate the specific information you may need about your accommodations.

neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is one of the city’s oldest neighborhoods. South Wedge is home to two historic districts and was once home to several historical figures including Frederick Douglass and jazz legend Cab Calloway. Today, South Wedge is one of Rochester’s trendiest enclaves. South Wedge merges the old and new with condos in renovated school buildings, brownstone apartments, modern townhomes, and colorful Edwardian and Victorian houses. The unique mixture of rental options is complemented by South Wedge’s vibrant murals and other forms of art (the area has the most public art in the city outside of the Neighborhood of the Arts).

South Wedge is also known for its strong sense of community. South Wedge has two neighborhood newspapers and several neighborhood organizations that hold popular events every year like Third Thursday Concerts and Night of the Living Wedge, a costume contest, and a pub crawl. The majority of South Wedge’s businesses are locally owned, adding to the close-knit

description: Enjoy the homey, private 3rd floor within our century-old home in a historic district (pls read full desc). neighborhood_overview:
Rochester and the surrounding area--from Lake Ontario to the Finger Lakes region--has numerous sights and activities to enjoy, and all of them are easy to get to from this airbnb space. Even Niagra Falls is just a 90-minute day trip.

The house itself is in a registered historic neighborhood with large homes from the late 1800s to early 1900s. It includes a mix of renovated homes, renovated tenant-occupied properties, and a smaller number of properties in process or need of renovation. This house sits on a tree-lined street nearest the park side of the neighborhood.

The location is 2.3 miles from Rochester General Hospital, near the Kodak facilities, and close to all downtown businesses. 15 minutes from the airport. 13 minutes from the University of Rochester. 15-17 minutes from Rochester Institute of Technology and Strong Memorial Hospital.

host_about:
I am a long time Rochester Resident. My love of travelling has taken me all over the world, but I always love coming back home to Rochester and its beautiful 4 seasons weather.

I am a professional photographer and you would enjoy some of my photographs in my properties.
I have seen my fair share of hotels and Airbnb houses on my travels around the world and understand the needs of fellow travellers. As a host, I can’t wait to show fellow travellers the same great hospitality that I have had across the globe.

My college town properties are located at a walking distance to the U of R and Strong memorial hospital, highland hospital and highland park. These are specifically organized to cater to professionals like physicians, nurses, medical students and other U of R visitors so they can live in a convenient place to work and can walk to their work or interviews etc. these are also well suited for guests visiting family locally or at these hospitals or coming to town for one of many festivals including world famous Lilacs festival. In all of our properties you will have the entire place to yourself. I am always available to answer any questions..

neighborhood_overview:
Charlotte is a quaint little community right on the edge of Lake Ontario! Home to the Ontario State Park (just a few blocks from your space) for swimming, picnic, and playground!

Also a few blocks away are many local favorite restaurants, both high end and "sports bar" environments, enjoy Abbotts Custard, and several attractions including a tour of the 1822 Charlotte Genesee Lighthouse!
If you're looking for things to do either while here or if you arrive early, check out my guestbook, I highly recommend Mr. Dominicks at the lake for great food and cocktails. Hose 22 or Windjammers are great local sports bars with fantastic food, beer and wine. Tour the Genesee lighthouse, stroll down the pier, enjoy Ontario State Park and ride on the genuine historic carousel!
host_about:
They say "Do what you love and call it work"  I love helping people find unique and unforgettable experiences that will make them smile when they look back on the memories for years to come. 

Personally, I want to live life to its fullest, I enjoy traveling to new areas, discovering new cultures (foreign and domestic) and meeting new and interesting people.  "Life is a book, those who don't travel have read only one page!"  Let me help you turn the page to new experiences!

"I'll look back on this and smile, because it was life, and I decided to live it"

neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing urban neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly).

The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco.

The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

The South Wedge also holds several popular festivals throughout the year. South Wedge-Ucation and the Harvest Hootenanny are held in S

neighborhood_overview:
Charlotte (pronounced shar-lot) is an amazing place filled with great restaurants, activities, desserts and most of all the LAKE! You're a short drive to the city to experience all the great things Rochester has to offer. Or head down the lake to hiking and bird watching spots that will have views for days.

Charlotte neighborhood enjoy the best of all possible worlds -- a scenic resort village situated inside a world-class city. A very active and cohesive Neighborhood Association completes the small-town feel. In summer, locals and visitors flock to Ontario Park Beach, music concerts and special events like the Rochester Harbor and Carousel Festival. Each winter, the Lakeside Winter celebration draws hundreds to the "Chilly, Chili Challenge" and "Polar Plunge."

name: 🤩STYLISH 2BR W/D, sunroom, close to UofR/Strong/DT
description:
WELCOME to your lovely, cute, comfy and safe home in the prime of Rochester! It's furnished with brand-new gorgeous contemporary furniture, art and decor while still providing a warm and cozy feeling.

This home is in the South Wedge district - one of the best, happening and safe locations. It's 1.5 blocks from South Ave with many bars, cafes and restaurants & very close to UofR, Downtown, Park Ave, East Ave, Highland Park. It's only 0.5 mile (2 mins) to 490 - so easy to get anywhere!
neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is one of the best neighborhoods in Rochester - super central and close to U of R, Strong Hospital, Downtown, Highland Park, Monroe Ave, Park Ave, East Ave, and Cobbs Hill Park. This home is a 1.5 blocks and a 3 min walk to South Ave - the street that runs from U of R to Strong to Downtown and has a lot of businesses including restaurants, bars and coffee shops.

From Niche.com:
"South Wedge is a neighborhood in Rochester, New York with a population of 5,023. South Wedge is in Monroe County and is one of the best places to live in New York. Living in South Wedge offers residents an urban suburban mix feel and most residents rent their homes. In South Wedge there are a lot of bars, restaurants, coffee shops, and parks. Many young professionals live in South Wedge and residents tend to be liberal."
host_about:
Good ole jolly couple traveling across the US and the world, and hosting in our homes in Indianapolis, IN and Rochester, NY and Las Vegas, NV.

We are a friendly, open-minded, outgoing, welcoming couple and we love hosting people from all around the world. We are both laid back, relaxed and empathetic. We are a bit of nomads and have lived in Los Angeles, San Francisco, San Diego, Las Vegas, Indianapolis IN, Boulder CO and Rochester NY. We hustle and work in the tech, entertainment and hospitality industry.

We like to keep an equal balance of work and recreation. While we mostly stay in during the week, we like to go out and do different activities on the weekends.

Truth be told, we're super easy to get to know, just ask away!

This area has experienced a surge of redevelopment, including new businesses, new housing at Carlson Commons and Plymouth Manor, and the University of Rochester's Brooks Landing Project, particularly Riverview Apartments.

In January 2012 UR announced that it was expanding the Brooks Landing Project to include yet more student housing. The new dormitory, located on Plymouth Ave (on the border between PLEX and the 19th Ward), is expected to be eleven stories high and home to 145-170 upperclassmen, in addition to the 400 already living in Riverview. A restaurant open to the public will occupy the first floor.

neighborhood_overview: The South Wedge is eclectic and creatively evolving- one of Rochester’s longstanding neighborhoods, home to two preservation districts, and some of the oldest houses in the city as well as renovated historic multi-family housing such as the Ellwanger-Barry School, which is now condominiums. From the South Wedge you can easily access Center City, Monroe Avenue, the University of Rochester and Medical Center, Mt. Hope Cemetery, and the Genesee River. Just around the corner are Highland Park and Genesee Valley Park. South Avenue carries a distinctive Brooklyn vibe with thriving businesses. You can attend a concert at the historic German House; have a drink or meal at one of the many bars, restaurants, or delis along South Avenue; schmooze with neighbors at a local coffee house; shop at various boutiques; drop in on a yoga class; at the South Wedge Farmers Market you can buy local and organic products.
host_about: Happy couple that enjoy both staying at home with our mixed family of kids and pets and also love traveling and often leaving them behind.

host_about: I’m a small business owner who lives in the South Wedge neighborhood near our two Airbnb properties. My partner, Jim, and I have enjoyed restoring our home and the Airbnb’s and have tried to maintain some of their original features and respect the era in which they were built. Our business, Historic Houseparts, is a retail business that specializes in architectural salvage, restoration supplies and vintage decorative accessories. We’ve used lots of our products in our houses. We also love to travel! So we’ve tried to make our houses feel like places we’d love to stay if we were traveling.

For those craving a little nightlife, local destinations cater to every preference. Visit Rochester’s Calendar for seasonal events that attract thousands. Please reference my guidebook for a list of local restaurants, bars, entertainment, parks, museums, sightseeing attractions, and other unique activities.

name: Private Bedroom and Bath with Separate Entrance
description:
This calm bed and bath in the back of our house on the SECOND FLOOR is a great place to stay while you explore Rochester. You enter through the back porch and MUST GO UP A FLIGHT OF STAIRS to the suite.

Located on the edge of the South Wedge/Highland Park area of Rochester it is walking distance to cafes, restaurants, Highland Park and the thruway 490.
It is easy to get to the local schools RIT, U of R, and the hospitals - as well as to downtown! Bus lines are close if you don't have a car.
neighborhood_overview:
You can walk up Mount Vernon at the corner for 10-15 minutes right into Highland Park. Designed by Frederick Olmsted, it is amazing.
If you head the other direction, toward downtown on South Avenue you will find a cafe, a new sushi bar, a co-op grocery store, and my favorite ice cream and chocolatier “the Hedonist.” There is often a line- but it moves well - and their homemade flavors and cones are great.
If you turn left toward Meigs from our house you can walk uphill to a back entrance to Highland Park, or turn left and find Dicky’s corner pub. I love their Friday fish fry! You can have it breaded, fried or grilled…
Farther down Meigs at South Clinton is a new restaurant called “Crisp,” and it gets great reviews...and it IS open on Sunday and Monday nights. Kitty corner from "Crisp" at the big old brick church is the Swillburger - with good burgers etc., a bar, and games! Ie. Pinball etc…
We also love Pizza Wizard, down South Clinton on the right one block (next
host_about:
I am a hatmaker (milliner), textile artist and grant writer, and I live in Rochester, NY.  My son Eli is a musician/videographer, and he sometimes lives here as well.  We like to go great places...we both have a lot of energy.  We both value creativity and respect that people have all kinds of various approaches to life. I believe that with consideration and communication we can figure it out so that everyone is happy.

I also teach felting classes, and indigo dyeing (shibori) classes - and hat making in my studio.  I like to have a bicycle to get around town for errands close by, and love walking my dog and getting to know neighbors and the neighborhood. 

I think it's important to get out and live life!  I also like to create safe and welcoming spaces to return to with textiles and art from around the world that are relaxing and beautiful.

neighborhood_overview:
This property is located in the South Wedge on Linden Street- a federally designated historic street. You'll find plenty to do within a short walk from the property (enjoy looking at all the funky painted houses and interesting architecture you see). Down the street on South Ave you'll find restaurants, bars and shopping. Going in the other direction on South Ave you'll see Highland Park (smell the famous lilacs if they are in bloom!) and Highland Hospital.

On Mount Hope Avenue (the other cross street) you'll see the Rochester Collegetown, which has plenty of shopping, bars and restaurants. If you continue down Mount Hope and fork left onto 15-A you'll find a Costco. If you continue in this direction you'll end up at Marketplace mall. Mount Hope also has a brewery nearby call Switfwater brewery.

Just a few minutes drive away you can find the Strong Museum of Play, the Rochester downtown, and one of the famous Wegmans Food Markets Stores.

name: •Picture Perfect Garden Suite
description:
Have your morning coffee (Or tea!) while looking out to a beautiful garden in the historic neighborhood of CornHill. Enjoy this cozy studio with elegant 11ft high ceilings send tons of light!

Long term stay? Message for discounted rate!

Our home, a landmarked 1870 Gothic Revival is the perfect home base for your stay in one of the city's most attractive neighborhoods, the Corn Hill Historic District! Close to major hospitals and universities such as Strong and UofR and minutes from DownTown!
neighborhood_overview:
There is no place like Corn Hill, with its famous Art Festival, beautiful architecture and amazing community based activities. Downtown is right around the corner, with Eastman Theatre, Geva Theatre, incredible dining and all the night life you could ask for, just a walk or short Uber ride away.

If you are in town for medical reasons, Corn Hill is a short ride from all major hospitals, such as Strong and Highland Hospital.

Rochester is the best, everything is close when you stay with us.

Corn Hill Landing, filled with cafes, bars and restaurants, along with downtown, are just a block away. Stroll the neighborhood and gaze at the architecture or walk the Genesee River Park for great views of downtown
host_about:
I’m an Architect turned Conference Interpreter, with a love for language and culture! Total museum and art geek and I love to sketch!!! Married to a Rochester boy!!!

I have an immense love of traveling and hope to see most of this planet during my lifetime.

neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing urban neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly).

The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco.

The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing urban neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly).

The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco.

The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

The South Wedge also holds several popular festivals throughout the year. South Wedge-Ucation and the Harvest Hootenanny are held in S

description: Welcome to the best of city living in one of Rochester’s most historical and eclectic neighborhoods -- Cornhill. The home is just off the Genesee Riverway Trail, with quick access to U of R, Strong, RIT, downtown & the South Wedge. Enjoy business or personal travel from a beautifully redecorated home with a private attached garage. Perfect for conventions, downtown festivities, campus visits, and house hunting. neighborhood_overview:
The centrally located Historic Cornhill district provides convenient access to best that Rochester has to offer -- from downtown businesses to boutique shops, theater to sporting events, and world-class concerts to innovative craft breweries. Amid stunning 19th Century architecture, the location affords nearby trails for running or strolling along the Genesee River. You can leave the car behind and find amazing cultural, dining, and networking opportunities just around the corner.

For those craving a little nightlife, local destinations cater to every preference. Visit Rochester’s Calendar for seasonal events that attract thousands. Please reference my guidebook for a list of local restaurants, bars, entertainment, parks, museums, sightseeing attractions, and other unique activities.

neighborhood_overview: The Upper Monroe neighborhood has all the ingredients essential to comfortable city living - retail, restaurants and recreation - within walking distance of the house. Its boundaries are marked at the north by Route 490, south at the city line with the Town of Brighton, east on Culver Road, and west to Field Street.  The Monroe Avenue Strip, inside the Monroe Upper Village, includes a pet store, shoe repair, family market, hair salon, a gaming store and much more. Many Upper Monroe neighbors enjoy the weekly walk to the Monroe Village Farmers' Market, held each Wednesday at the Blessed Sacrament Church parking lot at Monroe Avenue and Oxford Street. Cobbs Hill Reservoir is a quick walk, as well as hiking on beautiful Pinnacle Hill just a few blocks from your front door. Bordering neighborhoods, such as Highland, Swillburg and Park Ave, are also some of the nicest in Rochester.

The 19th Ward's motto—“urban by choice ”.
It boosts of it's rich racial, economic and ethnic diversity; professors and students from the University of Rochester and Medical Center, city officials and people from all walks of life. Architecture of the homes, originally designed for the working professionals of Rochester, attest to the beauty, style and sturdiness of these homes.

Green space abounds: Mark’s Park, on Westmoreland Drive along the historic Erie Canal, Eastmoreland Park and the Playground on Eastmoreland Drive. Highland Park’s urban arboretum and Frederick Law Olmstead's designed Genesee Valley Park, along with the Erie Canal Trail, afford leisure activities within walking distance.

South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing urban neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly).

The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco.

The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

host_about:
Hi! 
We’re glad you’re here. 
We just wanted to share a little bit about ourselves.
We are from the Philippines, born and raised. 
Joelle and I have known each other since 3rd grade — for a short stint. 
We reconnected again by going to the same high school. 
After high school, we got disconnected when I went to the US and she went overseas to UAE.
In 2017, we officially started a long-distance relationship. 
We managed it well that we’re now together in the US since 2018. 
We also now have a son and his name is Jagger who is the joy of our lives.
If we’re not on a road trip, we’re flying somewhere to travel. 
We love to keep our minds and perspectives fresh by experiencing different cultures, food, and people. 
We may just be starting out our journey but we hope to replicate our experiences by being an instrument for you, your friends, and your families to create beautiful moments staying at our properties.
We’re thrilled to be here and we hope to host you soon.

neighborhood_overview:
South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing urban neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly).

The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco.

The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

The South Wedge also holds several popular festivals throughout the year. South Wedge-Ucation and the Harvest Hootenanny are held in S

host_about: Hello my Name is Tim. I've always found passion in bringing people together and making them feel comfortable and understood. I also take pride in my ability to problem-solve and always being capable of finding a way to get things done. These two sets of qualities hopefully make me someone who can help you find a relaxing and convenient place to stay at a price point that works for you. I'm a life-time Rochestarian working with a locally owned and operated small short-term rental start-up, and we're exploring different avenues for bringing our high-quality, well-maintained properties to the right people who will treat our homes like their own, even if just for a short period of time. Regardless of their backgrounds, people are drawn to Corn Hill for its history, proximity (walking distance to downtown and the University of Rochester) and for its sense of community

The Corn Hill Neighbors Association is one of Rochester’s most active neighborhood associations, working hand in hand with city government and other neighborhood groups to provide for the continuing improvement of the neighborhood. neighborhood_overview: The South Wedge is said to be the fastest-growing neighborhood in the state outside New York City and is highly regarded for its strong sense of community. It boasts several neighborhood organizations and two newspapers (The Wedge and The South Wedge Quarterly). The majority of homeowners take pride in the neighborhood, and it has an ever increasing number of interesting shops and bars. Several streets are lined with multicolored "painted ladies" homes reminiscent of San Francisco. The South Wedge is also noted for having the most public art in the city outside the Neighborhood of the Arts. South Avenue and surrounding streets have a bright variety of art totems created by area artists, transforming parking meters into sculptures. In 2013 the Wall\Therapy project added nine murals to blank walls throughout the Wedge.

name: Luxury 4BR Urban Retreat: Ideal for Families
description: Relax in this newly renovated home located in the Browncroft Neighborhood of Rochester, New York.  Our home is convenient to highways and many shops, restaurants, and grocery stores are within walking distance.  The Buffalo Bills themed office, open concept living room and cozy bedrooms make for a perfect stay for families and friends.
host_about:
I grew up in Penfield, NY (suburb of Rochester) and attended college here at the University of Rochester (Go Jackets!).  After spending a few years living in Buffalo and Brooklyn, I moved back home in 2017. 

As a former college football player, my passions are pretty predictable: working out, college football & the NFL, and local cuisine.

I can't say enough good things about Rochester. I think the city gets a bad rep because of the cold winters, but the food scene, beautiful seasons, access to finger lakes, and sense of community is second to none. 

Ask me about my favorite brewery or favorite place to get a garbage plate :)

neighborhood_overview:
The beautiful Corn Hill Neighborhood is considered the “Oldest Residential Neighborhood in Rochester, NY”, and is also one of its most unique. We are located on the banks of the Genesee River and a short walk from our city’s business district.

Once known as the Third Ward, Corn Hill is a showplace of historic architecture, manicured streets and inviting parks. As a congenial and diverse community, we are committed to protect and promote the character of our area by nurturing goodwill and friendship among our neighbors.

Corn Hill is well known today for its annual events. Each August for two days, more than a quarter million visitors pack its narrow streets for the Corn Hill Art Festival which originated in 1968. Also, each summer, the Clarissa Street Reunion brings current and former residents together with visitors for a music-filled event on a street that was once referred to as “Rochester’s Broadway” because of its jazz clubs. I also take pride in my ability to problem-solve and always being capable of finding a way to get things done. These two sets of qualities hopefully make me someone who can help you find a relaxing and convenient place to stay at a price point that works for you. I'm a life-time Rochestarian working with a locally owned and operated small short-term rental start-up, and we're exploring different avenues for bringing our high-quality, well-maintained properties to the right people who will treat our homes like their own, even if just for a short period of time. We've gone above and beyond with our attention to detail in both the luxurious interior design, and the practicality and lived-in home feel necessary to feel comfortable in your short-term home away from home, If all of this sounds like a spiel, maybe it is. But the truth is, I want you to come and stay in our properties because I care about people, and I promise to show you that through our interactions, our communication, and our ability to provide you and your loved ones with a super comfortable place to live while you're here in my city, for whatever reason, and for however long you'd like.

neighborhood_overview:
A sprawling neighbourhood immediately east of Downtown Rochester, Alexander is named for the main thoroughfare in the area lined with restaurants, bars, museums, and apartments that range from affordable to upscale. Historic East Avenue is an upscale community with several stately mansions and diverse architectural styles such as Victorian, Art Deco, Italianate, and Gothic Revival. From the Rochester Museum & Science Centre to the George Eastman Museum to Memorial Art Gallery, there’s always something to explore in this historic part of Rochester. Locals enjoy strolling along East Avenue and surrounding streets to the many British and Irish-inspired pubs that give this neighbourhood a sense of nightlife just minutes from the city centre.

Minutes to all the major hospitals, such as Union, Strong Memorial and Rochester General.

12 minute drive to Rochester Airport.
